      "brief": {
        "ticker": "AGCO",
        "company": "AGCO Corporation",
        "what_they_do": "Global maker of agricultural equipment \u2014 high-horsepower tractors, combines, and precision-ag technology (brands: Fendt, Massey Ferguson, Valtra, PTx). [book]",
        "quarter": "Q1 2026 (reported May 5, 2026)",
        "company_brief": {
          "the_view": "A big Q1 earnings beat in a still-soft ag market \u2014 adj EPS $0.94 vs $0.44 consensus [book], on sales of $2,342.9M (+14.3% y/y, but only +4.7% ex-FX) [book]. The beat was driven by strong Europe (EME) margins, FX, a lower tax rate, and channel revenue that ran ahead of end-user demand \u2014 i.e. quality is mixed, not pure demand. Management RAISED the FY26 adj-EPS outlook to ~$6.00 (from $5.50\u20136.00) [book], hiked the dividend to $0.30, and announced $350M of Q2 buybacks. Yet the stock reaction was negative \u2014 the debate is whether the 1Q beat is durable or front-loaded, against a higher tariff bill (~$135M in 2026) and a softer Q2.",
