            "read": "a headline blowout, but read the quality: of the ~$0.50 beat, much is FX, tax, and channel revenue that 'ran ahead of end-user demand' [book]. Underlying ag demand is still soft (NA & Brazil retail tractor units down y/y); the real earnings power is the EME margin and the structural-cost program, not a demand recovery."
          },
          "guidance": "FY26 RAISED: adj EPS ~$6.00 (prior $5.50\u20136.00; ~$5.77 cons) [book]; net sales $10.5\u201310.7bn; adj op margin guide up. But it embeds a higher tariff cost of ~$135M in 2026 (+$90M y/y, and $25M above the prior estimate) on the Section 232 methodology change [book], and a softer Q2 (2Q EPS guide below the 1Q run-rate). The raise is mostly the 1Q beat + buyback flow-through, not a demand-led upgrade.",
          "sell_side": "Split desk on the SAME print [book]: Jefferies Buy $145 \u00b7 JPMorgan Overweight $143 \u00b7 Morgan Stanley Overweight \u00b7 BMO Market Perform \u00b7 Baird Neutral $120. Bulls: EME margin resilience, structural transformation, capital return, 'stress-case' valuation. Bears: beat is FX/tax/timing-aided, tariff headwind rising, demand still down, Q2 softer \u2014 hence the negative stock reaction despite the beat."
